<h1 style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 20pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 20pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7 Logging, Security, and More</span></h1>
<p style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">This section will cover the basics behind our plans for security and authentication.</span></p>
<h2 style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7.1 Security</span></h2>
<p style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Our customers privacy is our concern so we pledge to create an infrastructure that will help disguise and hide our subscriber&rsquo;s personal information. </span></p>
<p style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">One way of going about ensuring privacy on our site will be by using encryption. There will be many encryption options available to us as we get closer to deploying this feature on our site. Currently we have decided to make it a priority to encrypt the user&rsquo;s passwords, address, and credit card information. If need be later on, we might also encrypt the user&rsquo;s full name to ensure their anonymity. </span></p>
<p style="line-height: 2.4; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Another feature we will implement to ensure the user&rsquo;s security will be not to take information we do not need. It may seem obvious but many times a website or service will ask for information they never needed to have in the first place and this would just lead to more data being leaked if the service is compromised. For example, we will not be asking the user to access their microphones and cameras since our site has no use for these.</span></p>
